

                Angular -  Front End Technology


                        Bacic Commands
                1.to create a project - ng new project name/ng new project name --routing

                2.to run Angular Project - ng serve / ng serve --open

                3.to generate components - ng g c component-name

                3.to generate services - ng g c service-name


                                Basic Bulding Blocks

        1. Modules - To import 3rd party - (root module -AppModule)

        2.Component - To create html,css,ts file (root component - AppComponent)

        3.Data binding - share data inside component

                3.1. One way binding -data sharing only one direction

                        3.1.1 compenent(ts) to view(html)

                                3.1.1.1 String interpulation - {{expression}}

                                3.1.1.2 Property Binding - [attribute name]="Property Name"

                        3.1.2 View (html) to component(ts)

                                3.1.2.1 Event Binding (event name)="function-name()"

                                3.1.2.2 Event Binding using $event (event name)="function-name($event)"

                                3.1.2.3 Event binding Using template referencing variable - #variable name

                3.2. Two way binding -data sharing in both direction 

                        3.2.1. ngModel - import FormsModule in AppModule
                        -[(ngModel)]="property-name",property-name should defined in ts file


                4.Angular Routing - to set path for component in app-routing-modules  
                  -{path:value,component:class-name}
                  - use router - outlet selector inside a root component

                5. Dependency Injecnction - Share data between dependent classes

                6. ngSubmit - 

                7. Angular services  - to hold redundant data

                8. Angular Directives - to manipulate DOM

                        8.1 Component Directives

                        8.2 Structural Directive 

                                8.2.1 *ngFor -

                                8.2.2 *ngIf

                        8.3. Attribute Directive

                        9. Angular Forms

                                9.1 Template Driven Forms  - first design html

                                9.2 Model Driven Forms - first design ts file 

                                        9.2.1 Reactive Forms - Form Group , Array , Control
                                                - Add validations

                                                - import RecativeFormsModule

                        10. Local Storage

                                10.1 setItem
                                10.2 getitem
                                10.3 deleteItem

                        11.Parent Child Communication

                                11.1. parent to child  - @Input

                                11.2 child to parent - @Output

                        12.Angular Pipe

                        13.Front End - Back End

                                13.1 import HttpClientModule

                                13.2 Inject HttpClient





                
